Francis Sardauna in Katsina
Unidentified gunmen suspected to be kidnappers have reportedly killed a former Katsina State Commissioner for Education, Professor Halimatu Sadiya Idris along the Abuja-Kaduna road on Sunday. The suspected kidnappers were said to have attacked the former commissioner while returning from Abuja. The ministry’s Public Relations Officer, Salisu Lawal Kerau, who confirmed the death of the former commissioner in a statement issued yesterday, said her funeral prayer will hold today at Unguwar Sarki Kaduna. The deceased served under Governor Aminu Bello Masari as commissioner for education.